<p>&#8216;Four years on from submitting a complaint alleging she had been raped while in the armed forces, &#8220;Jane&#8221; is still awaiting a decision and says it was used as a &#8220;weapon&#8221; against her.<br />
She told the BBC that colleagues knew things about the confidential process &#8220;they should never have known&#8221;. Her concerns are not unique, according to a report by the ombudsman for armed forces complaints.&#8217;</p>
